## Resource Management

**Kimi K2 Model Limits (November 2025):**

- Maximum concurrent: 10 instances per orchestrator
- Typical usage: 7-10 for mixed complexity tasks
- Resource overhead: ~400MB RAM per instance
- Processing time: Variable (complex: moderate, simple: fast)
- Release: November 2025

**Performance Characteristics:**

**Complex Tasks:**
- Agentic AI coding: Moderate speed with autonomous problem-solving
- Multi-file refactoring: Good performance
- Complex integration: Efficient handling
- Autonomous workflows: Strong capability

**Simple Tasks:**
- CRUD operations: Fast execution
- Utility functions: Very fast
- Rapid prototyping: Fast
- Simple analysis: Fast
- 10 parallel Kimi K2: ~10x faster than sequential

**Cost Considerations:**

- Kimi K2 via LiteLLM is cost-efficient
- SAME MODEL for both complex AND simple tasks (simplified deployment)
- Open-source model without vendor lock-in
- 60-70% cost savings vs. Anthropic models
- Suitable for budget-conscious projects

